        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p><add>?</add>-rison with all our precepts of a kindred nature,- for that truth<lb/> is
                unchanging: they will stand in just and harmonious alliance<lb/> with the
                inspiration of old; for all true inspiration tends but to<lb/> a common purpose,-a
                perfect conviction of the duty we owe our<lb/> Maker for his assured justice, mercy
                and good will towards us.<lb/> If this inspiration be consistent with that of olden
                time, it will<lb/> also bring forth more light and knowledge on its great
                subject,<lb/> since we cannot suppose a revelation to be given but for a<lb/> useful
                end; and if it should bring no additional influence, it<lb/> could have no important
                effect.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">What I ask is, to be patiently indulged with attention until</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>the close of a series of articles setting forth the views, in regard to<lb/>
                <placeName>Israel</placeName> and the world, conferred upon me by spiritual
                impressions,<lb/> and which I have faithfully endeavoured to maturely
                investi-<lb/>gate, thoroughly understand and discreetly obey. If the
                opportu-<lb/>nity be afforded me, it will confer a lasting obligation; and if<lb/>
                after an ample exposition of these matters, they should be judged<lb/> erroneous or
                ill-founded, the result, apparently so lamentable, <add>?</add><lb/> be to me a
                signal gain, as I shall then stand relieved of the<lb/> momentous accountability of
                inculcating my views and opinions<lb/> upon my fellow man.</p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">G. B.</persName>
            </p>
            <p>Private Note</p>
            <p><addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>, D<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Sir, If this comm<hi
                    rend="sup">n</hi> will possibly bear insertion, you will greatly o-<lb/>blige me
                by its admission; &amp; in that case, please send me the N<hi rend="sup">o</hi>.
                containing it, &amp;<lb/> expect my subscription with the next article. Yours very
                faithfully <persName role="author">Geo. Barnard</persName>.</p>
        </body>
